# Kharchafy — Codex Instructions

## Stack
Vue 3 (`<script setup>`) · Pinia · Element Plus · Tailwind CSS · Vite · Firebase Realtime Database · Cloudinary

## Folder Layout
- `src/components/` — Vue SFCs (auth, groups, users, shared-expenses, shared-loans, personal-expenses, personal-loans, generic-components, layout)
- `src/scripts/` — composables backing each component, folder structure mirrors components/
- `src/stores/` — Pinia: authStore, groupStore, userStore, dataStore, tabStore
- `src/composables/` — useFirebase, useDebouncedRef, useApprovalRequests, useReceiptUpload, useGlobalNotifications, useLoginRateLimit, useUnsavedChangesGuard, useUsersOptions…
- `src/utils/` — string-formatting, maskMobile, sessionCrypto, queryCache, cloudinaryUpload, showAlerts, notifications…
- `src/helpers/` — approval checks, group membership tests
- `src/constants/` — DB_NODES (all Firebase Realtime DB path strings)
- `src/firebase.js` — Firebase init and re-exports

## Conventions
- Components are thin templates; state and handlers live in the paired script composable.
- Use `@/` alias for all `src/` imports.
- DB paths come from `DB_NODES` — never hardcoded.
- `String.prototype.toCapitalize()` capitalises every word (patched in main.js).
- `formatAmount` is injected via `provide/inject` — PKR currency formatter.
- Multi-member approval flows guard all destructive DB operations.

## Ignore
`node_modules/`, `dist/`, `dev-dist/`, `dist-ssr/`, `package-lock.json`
